## Introduction

In this article, you‚Äôll learn how to create a **CSS hover effect that dims all other list items except the one being hovered**.\
This technique uses the **CSS `:not()` pseudo-class** and works with **pure CSS ‚Äî no JavaScript required**.

This pattern is especially useful for navigation menus, lists, and UI elements where you want to focus the user‚Äôs attention on a single item.

