## The Problem

CSS makes it easy to style an element when it‚Äôs hovered. However, **dimming all sibling elements except the hovered one** is not as straightforward and is often solved with JavaScript.

The goal is to achieve this behavior:

- Hover one item
- Dim all other items
- Restore everything when the hover ends

We‚Äôll solve this using only CSS.

---

